The paper proposes a technique for domain generalization using deep neural networks and normalization layers. This technique is specifically applied to image classification tasks, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimizing the normalization layers for each domain, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the effectiveness of the proposed technique, which suggests that it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
